An Ilorin Magistratesâ€™ Court on Monday ordered that a vagrant, Sikiru Bolaji, for allegedly raping a 16-year-old girl, pending the outcome of an investigation. The police charged Bolaji with criminal force, intimidation and rape. Magistrate Ibijoke Olawoyin ordered that Bolaji be remanded in Oke-kura Prison, Ilorin. She adjourned the case until June 5 for further mention. The Prosecutor, Insp . Al-Hassan Jubril, alleged that the defendant beat up the victim and raped her at 11 p.m. while she was on her way foe a night vigil. Jubril said the offence contravened the provisions of sections 263, 396 and 282 of the Penal Code Law. The defendant pleaded not guilty to the charge.